Comparison of Geo, Disp new and Disp old Methods for event reconstruction
This is done by plotting the resolution per energy bin for various simulations. The resolution is the 68% containment radius of the data, from the source center.
Geo Method:
First: compare the calculation of resolution using 2 methods available: RMS and Res methods
RMS is calculated by calculating STD of the arrival angles.
Res is calculated by arranging all the events (those in the specified energy bin) in order of angle, then picking the 68% bin.
